Recovery (do this first)
The firmware itself is almost certainly intact — the problem is the saved sector and/or a fault-reboot loop. To be 100% clean, erase all flash, then reflash:


# hold BOOTSEL while plugging in USB so it mounts as RPI-RP2, then:
picotool erase        # wipes flash (clears the bad settings sector)
picotool reboot -u    # back to BOOTSEL
# then drag-drop the new build/VT100-PI.uf2 (I'm rebuilding it session-safe now)
If you don't have flash_nuke, picotool erase -a does the same. This clears whatever the save wrote.

